In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, favor is measured on the stats sheet and is a kind of advancement. Favor is visible on the stats sheet as a descriptive status. High favor grants tangible bonuses, such as access to skills and stat boosts.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, favor tiers are relatively broad and include: Strongly Disfavored, Disfavored, Neutral, Favored, Strongly Favored, and Paragon.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, low favor can significantly hamper an individual.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, pledges are permanent unless the god releases the human.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, some gods will dissolve the bond in the case of strong disfavor.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, wrathful gods may inflict horrible punishments.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, light consequences include restricted skills and lowered stats.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, severe consequences include physical ailments, injurious events, or even death.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the protagonist identifies a god to pledge to early on and works toward higher favor during the adventure.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, adherence to the god's tenets and successfully accomplishing things that the god approves of or that benefits the god increase favor.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, major transgressions can cause a rapid loss of favor.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, general living out of line with the god's tenets could cause a more gradual drop in favor.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, everyone starts as Neutral upon pledging to a god.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, Paragons are rare individuals who have lived lives in service to their god and thoroughly exhibit their virtues (or vices).

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, achieving the Paragon tier requires significant life achievements in service to their patron.
